<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-21T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="751" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51/1460: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-21T14:00:00+03:00">April
                                        21, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 21—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>995. To Wallace Murray from Landis. Have been informed by the British
                                that Jordan, British Minister to Saudi Arabia, will be in Cairo next
                                Monday for the Middle East Financial Conference. They say that
                                London after consultation with you has instructed Jordan to discuss
                                certain aspects of supply to Saudi Arabia with me. In the light of
                                the existing Saudi Arabian situation, I would be pleased to receive
                                any instructions that you may have on this matter.</p>
                            <p>Sent London as No. 44 repeated Department as No. 995. [Landis.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>